Date: 25 May 2002
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Dutch Ministry of Agriculture, Nature Management and Fisheries, BSE
file, press releases - 14 May 2002 [translated from Dutch and edited]
<http://www.minlnv.nl/bse/>

36th BSE case in the Netherlands
--------------------------------
On 13 May 2002, BSE was detected in an 8 yearold cow on a farm in Ubbergen
(Gelderland). This is the 36th BSE case in the Netherlands since 1997, and
the 8th in 2002.
The cow, Marie 49, born 9 May 1994, was slaughtered on 29 Apr 2002 in an
emergency slaughterhouse. It reacted positively to the rapid BSE test on 03
May 2002; this was confirmed in the laboratory on 13 May 2002. No clinical
signs have been observed among the other 101 cows on the farm. As usual, an
investigation is being carried out regarding the feeding on the farm, with
special reference to the feed given to the affected cow during her first
months of life.
All cows on the farm are to be destroyed. Animals that had been moved to
other farms are to be traced and destroyed as well.
